      <text bytes="721" sha1="1d2jkld50qwoyzvry2v9y4k20e1whdz" xml:space="preserve">=== Background ===
John has noted that in CDM, he introduced a notion of Coordinate System which is a set of maps defined independently of any variable. In xml, this would be something like this.
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;CoordinateSystem name="..."&gt;
&lt;map variable="var1"/&gt;
...
&lt;map variable="varn"/&gt;
&lt;/CoordinateSystem&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
==Rationale==
The argument for it is that sets of maps are often going to be used in identical form in a number of variables. Further, it allows one to add attributes to the coordinate system element to provide extra information.

==Proposal==
Do we add this element to the DDX?

==Discussion==
There seems no immediate hurry on this. It can be added rather transparently later on when a demonstrated need exists.</text>
